{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Completion Verification — PASS\n\nAll five acceptance criteria are met and the bug is resolved in the implementation. Evidence grounded in tool output follows.\n\n---\n\n### AC1 — Outbound differ emits parent CLEAR when locally detached but Jira still carries a parent\n\n**MET.**\n\n`outbound_differ.py:400-414` adds `result[\"parent\"] = None` in `_map_local_to_jira_fields` when `local_parent_id` is falsy and `emit_detach_clear=True`. `_diff_fields` (line 542) calls this mapper with `emit_detach_clear=True`. The parent branch at lines 607-623 then compares `None` against the extracted Jira parent key; when Jira has a stale epic-link and local is `None`, `None != jira_parent_key` is `True` and `changed[\"parent\"] = None` is emitted.\n\n---\n\n### AC2 — batch_dispatch.update_one routes the CLEAR through set_parent(key, None)\n\n**MET.**\n\n`batch_dispatch.py:418-422`:\n```python\n_has_parent_op = \"parent\" in fields\nparent_key = fields.pop(\"parent\", None)\nif _has_parent_op:\n    _call_with_retry(client.set_parent, issue_key, parent_key)\n```\nThe presence flag is checked *before* the pop so a `parent: None` CLEAR (key present, value falsy) correctly calls `set_parent(issue_key, None)`. The surrounding comment at lines 411-417 explicitly labels this \"Parent-detach churn fix.\"\n\n---\n\n### AC3 — Never-parented bound ticket (local None, Jira None) emits NO parent mutation\n\n**MET.**\n\nIn `_diff_fields` (lines 610-613), when Jira also carries no parent, `jira_parent_raw = jira_fields.get(\"parent\")` is `None` and `jira_parent_key = None`. The guard `if local_val != jira_parent_key` (line 614) is `None != None` → `False`, so nothing is added to `changed`. The regression test `test_never_parented_ticket_emits_no_parent_clear` in `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_parent_detach_sync.py` (lines 97-136) asserts this directly.\n\n---\n\n### AC4 — Same-pass inbound suppression prevents the inbound re-parent\n\n**MET.**\n\n- `inbound_differ.py:578-581`: `_OUTBOUND_TO_INBOUND_FIELD = {\"parent\": \"parent_id\", \"summary\": \"title\"}`.\n- `inbound_differ.py:633-644`: `_build_outbound_context` iterates outbound mutation field names and stores the *inbound* name (`\"parent_id\"`) in the context's `fields` set via the mapping.\n- `inbound_differ.py:720-723`: `compute_inbound_mutations` drops any inbound `changed` entry whose key is in `ob_entry[\"fields\"]`, so `\"parent_id\"` is suppressed whenever outbound emitted `\"parent\"` (including a CLEAR). This closes the oscillation loop for the detach case.\n\n---\n\n### AC5 — Regression test asserts outbound differ emits CLEAR (RED → GREEN)\n\n**MET.**\n\n`tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_parent_detach_sync.py` is a real, non-skipped, non-xfailed test file containing:\n- `test_detach_emits_outbound_parent_clear`: calls `compute_outbound_mutations` with a detached local ticket (parent_id=None) and a Jira snapshot carrying a stale `{\"key\": \"PROJ-EPIC\"}` parent; asserts the result contains a mutation for `PROJ-1` with a falsy `fields[\"parent\"]`.\n- `test_never_parented_ticket_emits_no_parent_clear`: asserts no parent mutation when both sides are parent-less.\n\nNo `pytest.mark.skip` or `xfail` markers are present.\n\n---\n\n### Bug resolution\n\nBoth root causes from the bug report are fixed:\n1. **Outbound never emitted a CLEAR** (original `parent_id` truthy-gate at line 364) — replaced by the `elif … emit_detach_clear` branch at line 400.\n2. **Inbound unconditionally re-applied the stale epic-link** — the `_OUTBOUND_TO_INBOUND_FIELD` mapping + `_build_outbound_context` + per-field suppression loop ensures `parent_id` is suppressed in the same pass that outbound emits a `parent` CLEAR.\n\n**Overall verdict: PASS — every requirement is satisfied.**"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782533090331780001,"uuid":"66cedf48-8501-4bff-8a66-1bf48750ce93"}